Czech Stocks: New World Resources, Pegas, Unipetrol Are Active

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-10-18T09:03:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/czech-stocks-new-world-resources-pegas-unipetrol-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
fell for a fourth day, retreating 0.2 percent to 915.9 by 10:50
a.m. in  Prague .  The following are among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP), the biggest producer of
coking coal in the country, slid 1.1 percent to 138.4 koruna,
its second day of declines.  Europe ’s benchmark coal futures
contracts slid 1.1 percent to $117.25 a metric ton in the
Netherlands, headed for their lowest close in eight months.  Pegas Nonwovens SA (PEGAS)  , the Czech maker of special
textiles used in health-care and hygiene products, stood at 419
koruna, versus 434 koruna at yesterday’s close. The stock traded
without the right to dividend for the first time today. With the
1 euro dividend removed, Pegas rose 2.4 percent.  Unipetrol AS (UNIP)  , the country’s biggest oil refiner,
fell 1.4 percent to 170.3 koruna. A close at that level would be
the lowest in more than two months. Unipetrol may discontinue
oil refining at its Paramo unit, Mlada Fronta Dnes newspaper
reported, citing Paramo chief Milan Kuncir.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  